BROWSER DUPLICATE-ON-RESUME FIXED playwriter-native (2026-06-02 ~19:30). USER REPORT: after idle then resume, the browser verb opened a SECOND browser, had to close both to recover. ROOT CAUSE: playwriter accumulates sessions across watcher lifecycles - when a watcher dies (silent-abort / supervisor peer-stale-takeover force-kill, established ~71x), its playwriter session stays in playwriter persistent registry (PLAYWRITER_HOME sock dir per cwd, survives watcher death), but the fresh watcher per-boot ports.json is empty so it cannot see the orphan -> getOrCreateBrowserSession session new spawns ANOTHER chrome -> duplicate. WITNESSED LIVE: playwriter session list showed 6-7 accumulated sessions (gm ids 2,3,6 + tv8 1,4,5,7) while gm ports.json tracked 0-1. CRITICAL USER CONSTRAINT: housekeeping must use HOW PLAYWRITER DOES IT, never a system-chrome OS query (Get-CimInstance chrome.exe / pgrep). FIX (plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js): reapOrphanBrowserSessions(pw,cwd,claudeSessionId,reason) = runBrowserRunner(pw, [session,list]) -> parsePlaywriterSessionList (table col1=ID col5=CWD) -> for each row where CWD==this cwd AND pwSessionId not active in ports.json -> runBrowserRunner(pw,[session,delete,id]). Wired at watcher-boot (runSpoolWatcher start), idle-sweep (60s browser-idle interval), and pre-spawn (getOrCreateBrowserSession before acquireProfileDir). NO OS chrome query. Note playwriter session new --direct AUTO-DISCOVERS existing CDP instances (could further dedupe). VALIDATED LIVE the playwriter way: playwriter session delete 2/3/6 returned Session N deleted, gm sessions 7->0; then fresh browser dispatch 7*6 -> [return value] 42 ok:true produced EXACTLY 1 gm session + 1 gm chrome port, no duplicate. node --check OK. DEPLOY NOTE: the supervisor reverts .gm-tools/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js to the PUBLISHED npm version on wrapper-sha drift, so a local cp to .gm-tools does NOT stick - this fix only goes live after commit -> cascade publishes gm-plugkit; cannot hot-deploy a wrapper edit, must publish.